The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for improving the performance of conversational agents in email-based communication. This falls under the domain of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques for entity extraction and intent detection. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural models for component level analysis in large documents, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV).
